<body class = "bg"> 
    <!-- 2 Panel Style. Left is Title, classifications and right is description-->
    <div class = "allWrap">
        <div class = "row">
            <div class ="bigTitle">Xpense</div>
        </div>
        <div class = "row">
            <div class ="subBigTitle">Small stuff adds up, so don't lose track of them!</div>
        </div>
        <div class = "row">
            <!-- Description section -->
            <div class = "col-md-6">
                <div class = "descriptionContainer">
                    <div class = "row">
                        <div class="descSubtitle">What it is</div>
                        <div class="descElab">
                            <p>
                                Xpense was made as a personal mobile solution to keep track of everyday expenses from coffee to visits to the mall. Every purchase can be recorded and displayed on the speedy interface, allowing for at a glance spending-habit analysis. It's also useful to know what purchases had caused my wallet to lighten so much!
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Data is stored in the cloud using Parse. 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                                        
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="descSubtitle">Motivation</div>
                        <div class="descElab">
                            <p>
                                There isn't an app in the market that allows for quick small expense tracking. There's Mint by Intuit, but I'd have to allow access to my credit card. Being such a hassle, I shy away from those apps. Other expense tracking apps do exist, but they suffer from having an overwhelming interface. 
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                "Expense Manager", a popular app on the appstore, inundates users with 9 dollar amounts (expenses and income annual, monthly, weekly) and 9 buttons. My app improves on this by creating a separate page for each time interval and allows users to swipe through them to achieve the desired scope. Users can further delve into their spending habits through the bottom button bar. 
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="descSubtitle">Source Code</div>
                        <div class="descElab">
                            Coming soon!
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <!-- Title, brief, photo section -->
            <div class = "col-md-6">
                <div class = "row">
                    <div class = "mediaContainer">
                        <div id="carousel-example-generic" class="carousel slide" data-ride="false" data-interval="false">
                            <!-- Indicators -->
                            <ol class="carousel-indicators">
                                <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
                                <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="1"></li>
                                <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="2"></li>
                                <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="3"></li>
                                <li data-target="#carousel-example-generic" data-slide-to="4"></li>
                              </ol>

                            <!-- Wrapper for slides -->
                            <div class="carousel-inner" role="listbox">
                                <div class="item active">
                                    <%= image_tag("xpense_main.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "carouImage") %>
                                </div>
                                <div class="item">
                                    <%= image_tag("xpense_expense.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "carouImage") %>
                                </div>
                                <div class="item">
                                    <%= image_tag("xpense_income.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "carouImage") %>
                                </div>
                                <div class="item">
                                    <%= image_tag("xpense_dues.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "carouImage") %>
                                </div>
                                <div class="item">
                                    <%= image_tag("xpense_new2.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "carouImage") %>
                                </div>
                                
                            </div>

                            <!-- Controls -->
                            <a class="left carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="prev">
                                <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                                <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
                            </a>
                            <a class="right carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">
                                <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                                <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
                            </a>
                        </div>
                        <!-- <div class = "row"> -->
                            <!-- <div class ="carouselContainer"> -->
                                
                            <!-- </div> -->
                        <!-- </div> -->
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class = "row">
                    <div class = "bulletContainer">
                        <div class = "row">
                            <div class = "col-md-3 text-center left_img">
                                <div class = "ci_cont">
                                    <%=image_tag("when_icon.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "circle_icon")%>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class = "col-md-9 right_descrip">
                                <div class ="iconBriefContainer">
                                    <p>Side Project</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class = "row">
                            <div class = "col-md-3 text-center left_img">
                                <div class = "ci_cont">
                                    <%=image_tag("materials_icon.png", :alt => "placeholder", :class => "circle_icon")%>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class = "col-md-9 right_descrip">
                                <div class ="iconBriefContainer">
                                    <p>Android Device</p>
                                    <p>Android Studio, Parse</p>
                                    <p>Java, XML</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>


